def: Having petals; as, a petaled flower; -- opposed to Ant:apetalous, and much used in compounds; as, one-petaled, three-petaled, etc.
To attempt to seize something suddenly; to catch; -- often withat; as, to snatch at a rope.
An animal, particularly a log, having an uncut tail. Cf.Curtail. Dog.
Destitute of water; as, anhydrous salts or acids.
The doctrines, principles, or practice of a mystagogue;interpretation of mysteries.
One who sheds blood; a manslayer; a murderer.
One of the curved lines () which inclose a parenthetic word orphrase.
